descriptionMarkdown:
96x96 Tiles, 3x3 Chunk Aligned Grids, built around the new big electric pole 32 tile reach. Most Prints fit onto of one another.
Normal Quality oriented. Please Report Problems, will try to keep updated. 

V.12 - 4302025
- Added Substation and Big Electric Power Pole to Chested Requester and Provider Station Prints for my Vanilla LTN Book to hook up with.

V.11 - -4292025
- Added more descriptions
- Fixed Titles

V.10 - 04282025
- Added Shuttle Station, Shuttle Terminal, Prescheduled Shuttle Train, and 96x Elevated Straight Way Shuttle Stop
- Added 96x Roboport EXT Upgrade Grid for heavier construction and logi bot traffic
- Added 96x Gleba Defense, Upgrade Mk2, a beefy Electric defense line.
- Increased and added more descriptions and better titles to some blueprints. 

V.9 -04272025

- Added Far Land Wall Resupply Station Blueprint

V.7

V.6

- added contact info, more notes, cleaned up previous comments.

V.5

V.2:
- Fixed Robo Grid misalignment
- Modified Titles for Better Recognition

Books:
- QElectro Bot Grids - Contains the base grids you would use for roboports, electrical, and defensives needs.
- QRails - Contains grids based on elevated main lines that work on any planet with appropriate research, with intersections and mergers for 1-8-1 maximum trains(You can go bigger with appropriate junction spacing,but 1-8-1 train length  fits nicely into 3 chunks.
- Fulgora E Grids - Contains Grids for Fulgora (Lighting Collectors cover a full Chunk)
- Gleba Grids - Defensive Grids for Gleba (Since walls and bullets are useless against max evo)
- Aquillo Grids - Heated Robo Grids
- Defense and Artillery Logistics and Supply

- Space Age Train Sizes - Train Configurations up to 8 wagon. 
- Extras - Stuff 

Notes:

4 way Intersection can't be placed ontop of straights. Needs fresh clearing. 
Any Artillery Outpost train should work on a time passed schedule, supply trains should work on limits when the outpost needs items.

I've been using these in my space age play through.The 4 way took me the most time to figure out how to squeeze into my grid and keep the roboports. Thanks to the community for all the ideas that went into this. 

Everything is based off the foundation of electrical and roboport coverage reach. So a 3x3 chunk grid fit my needs the best, you do lose the maximum logistic coverage, but I traded that for alignment. Nearly every single blueprint can accommodate this electric robo grid foundation.
Rails grids are based on the assumption of using Elevated Main lines everywhere, all of which can be placed atop the elevated straightway exception being the 4 way intersection. 

All Prints are Grid aligned except for the extras. All Grids should work well together when being laid ontop of each other with a few obvious exceptions
title: QGrids V.12 - Chunk Aligned Space Age Blueprints
